title: Roundup: Bruno gives Boonton last-minute victory
text:
Roundup: Bruno gives Boonton last-minute victory Staff Reports 9:53 p.m. EDT October 23, 2015 Pequannock goalkeeper Billy Troast stops Boonton's Frank Rau at point blank range during their NJAC-Independence boys soccer matchup. Pequannock won the game 3-2 in 2OT. October 22, 2015, Boonton, NJ. (Photo: Bob Karp/Staff Photographer) CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Senior Leia Bruno scored with 15 seconds to play, lifting Boonton to a 3-2 victory over Whippany Park in a NJAC-Independence field hockey game on Friday afternoon. Alexa Marzullo scored twice for the Wildcats (6-9-2). 
Roxbury 2, Parsippany Hills 0: Kayla Bedel-Franklin and Jaymie Fiebel each had a goal for visiting Roxbury (7-8-2). 
Pequannock 3, St. Elizabeth 0: Kaitlyn Natoli made one save for the shutout. Emiliana Hokr, Kate Weidmann and Lexi Toback each scored a second-half goal for Pequannock. 
Morristown-Beard 2, Mountain Lakes 1: Samantha Chanzit led the Crimson (13-5) with a goal and an assist. Holly Smith scored Mountain Lakes' goal in the second half. 
Mount Olive 4, Morris Hills 1: Alyssa Borozan, Rachel Jeska, Frankie Pignataro and Kira Steinmark scored for host Mount Olive (12-5). Jenna Gallagher had a second-half goal for Morris Hills (3-12). 
Morristown 7, Vernon 0: Sophomore forward Callie Sundin had two goals and an assist. Sophomore midfielder Devon Colquhoun added a pair of goals. 
Sparta 4, Pope John 1: Alexis Gudenkauf scored twice for visiting Sparta (11-7-1). Ali Sturchio had a first-half goal for Pope John (1-17). 
Boys soccer 
Whippany Park 2, Kinnelon 0: Senior Ryan Gaynor made eight saves for his third shutout (5-10-1). Tom Rigas and Pat Thompson scored Whippany Park's goals. 
Morris Catholic 5, Morris Tech 0: Senior Bryan Medina led Morris Catholic with a hat trick and an assist. Senior Tyler Valle made four saves for his third shutout. 
Madison 3, Mountain Lakes 0: Mike Noto made three saves for his third shutout. 
Girls soccer 
Hanover Park 2, Villa Walsh 1: Gianna Zarra scored both Hanover Park goals. Alyssa Yarosz scored in the first half for Villa Walsh (12-6-1). 
Morris Catholic 9, St. Elizabeth 1: Sarah Racine led Morris Catholic (14-2-1) with four goals and two assists. Claire McVicar scored a first-half goal for St. Elizabeth (1-12). 
Tennis 
Morris Hills 3, Roxbury 2: Singles: Casey Hascup (R) def. Vasha Sedlacek 6-2, 6-2 ; Aakriti Mathur (MH) def. Alexis Andersen 6-0, 6-0; Katrina Abad (MH) def. Autumn Manche 6-2, 6-0 ; Doubles: Jade Manche and Kaytlynn Chey (R) def. Lipika Rana and Ashley Ayers 6-2, 6-2; Manal Waseem and Jan Ramos (MH) def. Neema Njoroge and Naria Rush 6-1, 6-0. Team records: Morris Hills 12-7, Roxbury 2-15. 
Chatham 4, Summit 1: Singles: Scarlett Blydenburgh (C) def. Mae Hoad 6-1, 6-3; Seden Agar (C) def. Ali Demakos 6-3, 6-2; Laurel Hickey (C) def. Nicole Del Rosso 6-2, 6-2 ; Doubles: Lana DePasquale and Julia Gallop (C) def. Kendall Blomfield and Danielle Del Rosso 6-2, 7-6 (7-3); Alisha Kewalramani and Rachel Schwartz (S) def. Jen McCann and Abby Morgan 4-6, 6-3, 10-7. Team records: Chatham 14-4, Summit 13-7. 
Volleyball 
HWS: Hackettstown 2, Delaware Valley 1 (24-26, 25-17, 25-15): Hackettstown (18-5): Nioami Miranda 11 kills, 2 blocks, dig, assist, ace; Rylee Legreide 3 aces, 15 assists, 9 digs, block, kill. 
North Hunterdon 2, Pope John 0 (25-9, 25-21): Pope John (6-13): Grace Parker 2 kills, 6 digs; Kristyn Spetz 14 digs. North Hunterdon (10-7): Sarah Jennison 6 kills, 4 digs, 4 aces. Read or Share this story: http://dailyre.co/1LTk7sE TOP VIDEOS
